          FAQ
        </span>
        <h2 class="reveal d-1">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="reveal d-2" style="max-width: 450px; margin: var(--space-sm) auto 0;">
          Everything you need to know about HTMLWallarper.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Does this work with other desktop environments?</span>
            <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Currently, HTMLWallarper is designed specifically for <strong>KDE Plasma</strong> which has built-in HTML wallpaper support. Other desktop environments may require additional tools or plugins to render HTML wallpapers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Will this drain my battery on a laptop?</span>
            <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Our wallpapers use <strong>CSS-only animations</strong> that are GPU-accelerated. This means minimal CPU usage and negligible battery impact. Most wallpapers consume 0% CPU at idle.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I create my own wallpapers?</span>
            <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Absolutely! Each wallpaper is just a single <code>index.html</code> file. You can copy an existing wallpaper and modify it, or create one from scratch. We welcome contributions via Pull Request!</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I customize colors and animations?</span>
            <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Open the <code>index.html</code> file in any text editor. Look for CSS custom properties (variables) at the top of the <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> block. Change colors, speeds, and other values, then save and refresh.</p>
